ase success, and at least one basic conflict scenario.","reasoning_effort":"high","depends_on":["ST2","ST3"],"owned_paths":["tests"],"success_criteria":"The repository contains automated tests that locally verify each required workflow end to end, including both normal cases and at least one merge or rebase conflict case."},{"step_id":"ST5","task_title":"Publish README and Static Website","display_description":"Document lit with a concise README and simple English local website.","codex_description":"Create a lightweight documentation surface with no heavy site stack: add a concise `README.md` and a simple static English website that explains what `lit` is, why to use it, local/offline-only constraints, installation and setup, quick start, command overview, example workflows, Git similarities and differences, and current limitations honestly.","reasoning_effort":"medium","depends_on":["ST2","ST3"],"owned_paths":["README.md","website"],"success_criteria":"A new developer can read the README or open the local website and find accurate English instructions for installing, running, and understanding `lit`, including its supported workflows, local-only design, and non-goals."}]}
